\n<Radro>Yes, yes! If you dig a hole, make sure to fill it back in!
We can't have someone falling and getting hurt, right?
1ラドロP照れ

\n<Radro>Aventus is a child who recently arrived, and it seems like
their emotional wounds haven't healed yet.
1ラドロP困惑

\n<Radro>The feelings of a child abandoned by their parents... I've
been there before, but I wonder how I can save them.
1ラドロP笑い3

\n<Radro>Do you think it's strange to run an orphanage in a place
like this? It's necessary because it's a place like this.

\n<Radro>There are so many tough things, but when I see the

\n<Radro>It's not the time to be tired. Having something that only I

\n<Radro>This town, Drine, is called a "dumping ground." People
living above throw away things they no longer need.
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>To them, we might just be "ants swarming over spilled ice
cream." In fact, we sometimes wait for usable things to fall
down.
1ラドロP普通

\n<Radro>I wonder what kind of adults these children will become. The
public order is bad, it's dirty, and I can't provide them
with a proper education, but still, I have hope.
1ラドロP笑い3

\n<Radro>I was taught a lot of kindness by "Mama." So, even in a
place like this, no matter how dirty it gets, I want to pass
that on to these children.
1ラドロP普通2

\n<Radro>Hey hey, cat beastfolk are cute, aren't they♥ I wish I had
ears like that. And a tail would be nice too. Can I touch
it?
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>I won't pry if you don't want me to, but you come from a
prestigious family, right? Are you really okay with being in
a place like this?
1ラドロP普通

\n<Radro>If you have a place to return to, you should go back
properly, you know? Well, I'm sure there are various
circumstances so I won't say anything more.

\n<Radro>The other day, right? Trash thrown from above almost hit a
child and I just snapped! Went up there to give them a piece
of my mind!
1ラドロP困惑

\n<Radro>Then they sincerely apologized and even gave me money...
They were really nice people, and somehow, I couldn't stay
mad at them.
1ラドロP照れ

\n<Radro>Maybe the one who was discriminating based on where we live
was me after all.

\n<Radro>It's a town with bad public order and lots of drunkards and
criminals, but everyone is kind when it comes to the
orphanage. The previous "Mama" was a very good person.
1ラドロP笑い2

\n<Radro>Mama was quite the drinker too. In the end, she died from
liver problems. But still, I will carry on her will.

\n<Samuel>Dig dig dig... If I dig a hole here, some really gross bugs
come out. I'll show them to you when they do.

\n<Constance>Radro is really good at cooking! She praises me a lot
if I eat everything without leaving anything behind, but I
can't leave any even if I wanted to! Because it's so
delicious!

\n<Constance>But then, Samuel starts teasing me saying, "You'll get fat,"
and that always leads to a fight. I don't even want to
fight!
\n<Aventus>...
\n<Boy>Look at this bug! It's freakin' disgusting!
\n<Girl>Stop it! The way it wriggles its legs is so gross, nooo!
